  "prompt": "Where can I get an explainer video for $100?",
  "response": "Finding an explainer video for $100 can be challenging, as professional explainer videos typically cost more due to the amount of work involved. However, here are some options you could explore:\n\n1. **Freelance Platforms**: Websites like Fiverr, Upwork, and Freelancer often have creators who offer budget-friendly services, including explainer videos. You can search for freelancers within your budget and check their reviews and portfolios.\n\n2. **Local Creators**: Reach out to local animation or video production students or professionals who might be willing to create an explainer video for less money to build their portfolios.\n\n3. **Online Tools and Software**: There are online tools like Powtoon, Vyond, and Animaker that allow you to create your own explainer videos using templates and pre-made assets. These platforms offer affordable plans that might fit your budget.\n\n4. **Social Media and Forums**: You can post your request on social media platforms like Facebook, LinkedIn, or Reddit in relevant groups or forums. Sometimes, creators who are starting out are looking for opportunities to showcase their skills and might offer lower rates.\n\nBe sure to communicate clearly about your project needs and expectations to avoid misunderstandings.",
